.TH XCONNECTCTL 1 "July 2026" "2.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xconnectctl \- Command-line control tool for xconnect KDE Connect daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xconnectctl
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBxconnectctl\fR is the command-line utility for \fBxconnect\fR, a lightweight Vala/C implementation of the KDE Connect protocol. It allows managing device pairings, sending files, URLs, text, and SMS messages, and controlling systemd service execution directly from the shell.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list-devices
Lists all paired and discovered devices on the local network along with their status (Paired/Unpaired, Active/Offline) and IP address.
.TP
.B show-device \fIPATH\fR
Displays detailed properties and advertised capabilities of the specified device object path (e.g. \fI/org/xconnect/device/0\fR).
.TP
.B show-battery \fIPATH\fR
Displays battery level percentage and charging status for the specified device.
.TP
.B pair-device \fIPATH\fR
Initiates a pairing request to the specified device and outputs the 8-character verification key for security matching.
.TP
.B accept-pair \fIPATH\fR
Accepts an incoming pairing request from the specified device.
.TP
.B reject-pair \fIPATH\fR
Rejects an incoming pairing request from the specified device.
.TP
.B allow-device \fIPATH\fR
Grants permanent access permission to a device.
.TP
.B remove-device \fIPATH\fR
Removes a device completely from the configuration cache.
.TP
.B find-device \fIPATH\fR
Rings the remote phone at full volume to locate it.
.TP
.B share-url \fIPATH\fR \fIURL\fR
Opens the given web URL in the remote device's default web browser.
.TP
.B share-text \fIPATH\fR \fITEXT\fR
Sends a text snippet to the remote device.
.TP
.B share-file \fIPATH\fR \fIFILEPATH\fR
Transfers a file to the remote device's downloads folder.
.TP
.B send-sms \fIPATH\fR \fINUMBER\fR \fIMESSAGE\fR
Sends an SMS text message using the remote phone.
.TP
.B start-daemon
Starts the \fBxconnect.service\fR user systemd service.
.TP
.B stop-daemon
Stops the \fBxconnect.service\fR user systemd service.
.TP
.B help
Displays command usage and available options.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-debug
Enables debug logging output.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enables verbose output.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Shows command-line option help.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xconnect (1)
